# Clean Code Rules

## Naming
- Names self-explanatory, readable as English. NO single-letter except loop counters.
- Booleans: prefix `is`, `has`, `should`, `can`.
- Functions: start with a verb.
- Class / Type: PascalCase, noun.
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.

## Functions
- ≤ 20 lines (target).
- ≤ 3 parameters (target).
- Single Responsibility.
- NO hidden side effects.

## Comments
- Code self-documents first. Comments explain **why**, not **what**.
- DO NOT comment-out code.

## Error handling
- Catch at boundaries. Each error has a concrete code/type.
- NEVER `throw new Error("something went wrong")`.

## Magic values
- Extract into named constants instead of magic numbers/strings.

## Dead code
- Remove unused imports / variables / functions.

## File size
- ≤ 300 lines (target).

## Imports
- Group: stdlib → third-party → internal absolute → relative.
- NO circular imports.
